      <refmeta>
        <refentrytitle>http_param
</refentrytitle>
        <refmiscinfo>ws
</refmiscinfo>
      </refmeta>
      <refnamediv>
        <refname>http_param
</refname>
        <refpurpose>returns value of a HTML form parameter in VSP context
</refpurpose>
      </refnamediv>
      <refsynopsisdiv>
        <funcsynopsis xml:id="fsyn_http_param">
          <funcprototype xml:id="fproto_http_param">
            <funcdef>
              <function>http_param
</function>
            </funcdef>
            <paramdef choice="opt">in 
<parameter>name
</parameter>

   varchar
</paramdef>
          </funcprototype>
        </funcsynopsis>
      </refsynopsisdiv>
      <refsect1 xml:id="desc_http_param">
        <title>Description
</title>
        <para>This function is used to return value of a HTML form parameter in VSP context.
	  It's almost like call get_keyword ('name', params) used in VSP programming.
	  When 'name' parameter is not supplied, the result of http_param() call will be
	  all parameters, as they are contained in 'params' parameter of the VSP pages.
	  This function is useful in HTTP authentication PL hook, as in this place there
	  is no 'params' argument.

</para>
      </refsect1>
      <refsect1 xml:id="params_http_param">
        <title>Parameters
</title>
        <refsect2>
          <title>name
</title>
          <para>A string with name of the parameter to return
</para>
        </refsect2>
      </refsect1>
      <refsect1 xml:id="ret_http_param">
        <title>Return Types
</title>
        <para>
	  Returns value of a HTML form parameter, or array of all parameters.
</para>
      </refsect1>
